On February 8, 2019, former Representative John David Dingell Jr., the longest-serving Member of Congress in US history, passed away. In honor of his memory and service, President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation ordering that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at the White House, all public buildings and grounds, military posts, naval stations, naval vessels, and other federal government facilities in Washington D.C., throughout the United States, and its territories and possessions until sunset on February 9, 2019. The proclamation also directed that the flag be flown at half-staff for the same period at all US embassies, consular offices, military facilities, and naval vessels and stations abroad. The proclamation was signed by President Trump on February 8, 2019.